<TITLE> Shahjalal university opens on Sept 10 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, Sep 5 (bdnews24.com)  Classes resume in the Shahjalal University of Science and Technology on September 10 after nearly three weeks of shutdown The syndicate, the highest decision-making body of the university, set the date in a meeting Wednesday, vice-chancellor M Aminul Islam told reporters. All student dormitories will be re-opened on September 8, the meeting decided. Authorities will announce fresh schedule for the stalled examinations immediately after the resumption, according to the meeting decisions. "The situation is quite normal here compared to other universities. So we have decided to resume academic activities," Islam told bdnews24.com. On Sept 22, the government closed all universities in the wake of the bloodiest campus violence in more than a decade that broke out in Dhaka University before spreading to other universities and streets of major cities. bdnews24.co
